In [23]:
def plot_distribution_by_type(country):
    plt.rc("figure", figsize=(20, 10))
    b = sns.lineplot(x = "username", y = "username_count", data = df[df['country'] == country], hue="type")
    loc = plticker.MultipleLocator(base=10.0) # To put a tick every seven days
    b.axes.set_title(f'Tweets distribution by type : {country}', fontsize=30)
    b.set_xlabel("Date",fontsize=20)
    b.xaxis.set_major_locator(loc)
    b.set_ylabel("Number of tweets",fontsize=20)
    b.tick_params(labelsize=15)
    plt.legend(labels=['Media', 'Politics'], fontsize = 20)
    plt.show()
In [28]:
countries = df.country.unique().tolist()
for country in countries:
